title.idno: List of authors, contributors to discussions assembled in the corpus "Conflits dans le Wikipédia francophone" (cmr-wikiconflits)
title.desc: All users who participated in the thematic articles of cmr-wikiconflits-tei-v1 or in the discussions linked to these themes are identified in a single TEI file. The contributors' identification codes and their usernames have been collected using both manual and automatic processing techniques described in the previous section. This task was completed keeing the inconsistencies that appear in Wikipedia pages in mind and to comply with quality criteria regularly used when building linguistic corpora (one single identification code for each participant throughout the whole corpus.) All contributors have been collected and identified in this TEI file. Every TEI file in the corpus will therefore contain explicit links to this document when an identification code is used to identify a contributor to an article or to a discussion.

Tous les utilisateurs ayant participé à tous les articles des thèmes de cmr-wikiconflits-tei-v1 ou à toutes les discussions liées à ces thèmes sont rassemblés dans ce seul et unique fichier TEI. L'identifiant des contributeurs, ainsi que leur pseudonymes ont été rassemblés grâce aux traitements automatiques et manuelles décrits dans la section précédente.

Ce travail a été accompli au vu des inconsistances apparaissant dans les pages Wikipédia et, enfin, pour répondre à un critère qualité habituel dans l’élaboration des corpus en linguistique (un et un seul identifiant pour le même participant dans tout le corpus). Tous les contributeurs ont été rassemblés et identifiés dans ce fichier TEI unique. Chaque fichier TEI du corpus va donc explicitement renvoyer à ce document lorsqu’il s’agit d’identifier les contributeurs pour un article, comme pour une discussion.

notesStmt.note: All the contents related to authors / contributors to the Wikipedia pages and discussions selected in the corpus cmr-wikiconflits-tei-v1 include the following elements

ref.desc: This TEI file which lists the 3971 authors and gives them an ID

Selection of 360 pages (authors' pages + their discussion pages) of authors who have at least contributed 10 times to one of the pages or discussions related to our corpus. XML files have been left as-is, i.e. in wikicode / wikitexte formats.
Spreadsheet containing numbers of authors / contributors per topic ; per topic list of authors and contributors with their frequencies.
Manual, written in French, which explains what part of Wikipedia.fr have been selected and what automatic processing has been done on dumps.

projectDesc.p:
Every author / contributor to the whole corpuscmr-wikiconflits-tei-v1 is given here a unique identifier in order to allow automatic processing throughout the whole corpus. There exists different types of users:
an author / contributor is a registered user of Wikipedia. The Wikipedia system has given him/her an ID. S/he may appear with several username (following Wikipedia terminology), an alias used when signing her/his contribution.
an author / contributor is not registered, but identified by Wikipedia with her/his Internet number (IP)
an author / contributor whose username appeared in signatures may have disappeared from the Wikipedia system
an author / contributor has not be recognized by Wikipedia, nor in our processing

in order to use contributors' IDs, every TEI file in the corpus must include in its teiHeader the following statement:

In the context of the project Wikiconflits, private URIs with the prefix "psn" point to person elements in the projects's cmr-wikiconflits-contributors-tei-v1.xml file.

 . In the corresponding files, the who will contain the contributor's ID with the prefix psn:See TEI-P5 guidlines , chapter 16 "Linking, Segmentation, and Alignment", section "Using Abbreviated Pointers"

segmentation.p: The body part of this file is presented as in the usual particDesc of TEI file with one person per author / contributor
